Definition:
A flowchart is a diagram that shows the step-by-step flow of a program using symbols.

Why Use?

Easy to understand logic

Helps in planning before coding

Great for beginners

Main Symbols:

| Symbol Shape     | Name           | Example in Class       | Purpose                       |
| ---------------- | -------------- | ---------------------- | ----------------------------- |
| ðŸ”µ Oval          | Start / Exit   | `Start`                | Start or End the program      |
| ðŸ”¶ Parallelogram | Input / Output | `Read N`, `Print "Hi"` | Take input or show output     |
| â–­ Rectangle      | Process        | `name = "Shradha"`     | Do some operation/calculation |
| ðŸ”· Diamond       | Decision       | `is marks > 33?`       | Yes/No type condition check   |
| âž¡ Arrow          | Flow Arrow     | â†’                      | Shows the direction of steps  |


